AGI -&nbsp;Part of a 10-storey residential building collapsed in the south-west of Belgorod after being damaged by the debris of a fallen Ukrainian bullet. They let the Russian authorities know what the Tass reports. 19 wounded have been reported so far, but the number could increase further.
<br> According to Russian media Ukrainian forces launched rockets on Belgorod and surroundings from morning to fifth time throughout the day. Around 11:40 hours in Moscow, Ukrainian forces attacked Belgorod's residential areas with Tochka-U missile systems, Vilkha MLRS and Czech RM-70 Vampire systems, reported the Russian Ministry of Defense. The Russian air defense shot down the bullets, but the debris of one of the Tochka-U missiles damaged the building. After the fall of the debris of a broken rocket, the ten-story condominium collapsed. The entire building has been damaged and at least 16 apartments have completely collapsed.
&nbsp;
Russia has called on the OSCE leadership, starting with the Maltese presidency in turn, to condemn "the terrorist attack of the Kiev regime against the peaceful areas of Belgorod, which has caused dozens of victims". Ria Novosti writes it.
&nbsp;
"Today's brutal terrorist attack by the Kiev regime against the peaceful areas of Belgorod, which has caused dozens of victims, was carried out using weapons provided by NATO countries. We ask the OSCE leadership, in particular the Maltese Presidency, to condemn it as hard as possible," we read in the statement of the Russian Permanent Mission to the OSCE.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
<h2> Extract two bodies
The bodies of two victims were extracted from under the rubble of the building partially collapsed in Belgorod following an attack by the Ukrainian forces. He writes it on his channel Telegram the governor Vyacheslav Gladkov quoted by Ria Novosti. "Identity is under investigation. An investigative commission is working on the spot," wrote the governor of the region.
